# Kruda Framework — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Go web framework at github.com/go-kruda/kruda
- Go 1.24+ required, zero external deps in core
- Build/test: `go test -tags kruda_stdjson ./...`

## Code Style
- All exported types/functions must have doc comments
- Functional options pattern: `WithXxx(value) Option`
- Method chaining: methods return `*App` or `*Ctx`
- Error handling: return `*KrudaError` or `error`
- Use `slog` for logging, never `fmt.Println` or `log`

## Patterns
- Handlers: `func(c *Ctx) error` or typed `func(c *C[T]) (*Out, error)`
- Middleware: `type MiddlewareFunc = HandlerFunc`
- DI: `Give(value)` to register, `Use[T](container)` to resolve
- Resources: implement `ResourceService[T]` interface for auto CRUD
- Tests: white-box (same package), PBT files use `_pbt_test.go` suffix

## Import Order
1. Standard library
2. `github.com/go-kruda/kruda/...` (internal packages)
3. External dependencies (only in cmd/kruda and contrib)

## Don'ts
- Don't add external dependencies to core package
- Don't use `interface{}` — use `any`
- Don't use `init()` functions
- Don't break Phase 1-4 public API

## References
- Spec: docs/kruda-spec.md
- Architecture: CLAUDE.md
